<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id83d29496-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s2306"><num value="2306">§ 2306.</num><heading> Openness of meetings</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Administrator by regulation shall require that—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83d29497-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s2306/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> formal meetings of the Office of Federal Procurement Policy, as designated by the Administrator, for developing procurement policies and regulations be open to the public; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="id83d29498-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2" identifier="/us/usc/t41/s2306/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> public notice of each meeting be given not less than 10 days prior to the meeting.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="id83d29499-3a70-11f1-ab1a-a784e0a454e2">(<ref href="/us/pl/111/350/s3">Pub. L. 111–350, § 3</ref>, <date date="2011-01-04">Jan. 4, 2011</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/124/3737">124 Stat. 3737</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
